# Pinned Cal.com (Cal.diy) upstream source for per-clinic image builds.
# Read by CI (Cal.com image-build workflow) and by DEPLOY.md §8 local builds.
# Rationale, build args, and the ref decision: see CALCOM_IMAGE.md.
#
# Decision: pin `main` to a commit SHA to get the MIT-licensed community edition
# (the newest *tag*, v6.2.0, is still AGPLv3+ee — no MIT tag exists yet).
#
# Bumping Cal.com = update CALCOM_SHA, then RE-VERIFY the LICENSE at the new SHA
# is still MIT before building (the whole point of pinning main is clean MIT).

CALCOM_REPO=https://github.com/calcom/cal.diy.git
CALCOM_REF=main
CALCOM_SHA=f00434927386c9ecdcbd7e6c5f82d22044a245bc

